{{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Sweden}} "Alla andra får varann" | image = | caption = | year = 1960 | country = Sweden | artist = [[Siw Malmkvist]] | as = | with = | language = Swedish | languages = | composer = Ulf Kjellqvist | lyricist = [[Åke Gerhard]] | conductor = Thore Ehrling | place = 10th | points = 4 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1960se from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Augustin | prev_link = Augustin (song) | next = April, April | next_link = April, April }} '''"Alla andra får varann"''' (All the others get each other) is a song by [[Sweden|Swedish]] singer [[Siw Malmkvist]], that represented Sweden at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1960]], performed in [[Swedish language|Swedish]].
The song was the winner of [[Melodifestivalen 1960]], performed by both [[Östen Warnerbring]] and [[Inger Berggren]]. However it was decided by [[Sveriges Radio]] that Siw Malmkvist would perform the song at Eurovision. Siw Malmkvist never released her version either as a single or as an album track. The song was released by [[:sv:Mona Grain]].
The song was performed second on the night of the contest, held on 29 March 1960, following the [[United Kingdom]]'s [[Bryan Johnson (singer)|Bryan Johnson]] with "[[Looking High, High, High]]" and preceding [[Luxembourg]]'s [[Camillo Felgen]] with "[[So laang we's du do bast]]". The song received 4 points, placing 10th in a field of 13.
The song was succeeded as [[Sweden in the Eurovision Song Contest|Swedish representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1961|1961 Contest]] by [[Lill-Babs]] with "[[April, April]]".
