'''Badinogo''' is a village in the [[Kongoussi Department]] of [[Bam Province]] in northern [[Burkina Faso]]. It lies to the north of [[Kongoussi]]. It has a population of 800.<ref>[http://www.inforoute-communale.gov.bf/list_vill/centre_nord.htm Burkinabé government inforoute communale] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070324205443/http://www.inforoute-communale.gov.bf/list_vill/centre_nord.htm |date=March 24, 2007 }}</ref> It is sometimes listed as '''Badinogo-1''' to distinguish it from the smaller village [[Badinogo-2]] to the west of Kongoussi.
