'''Chernobyl Way''' ({{lang-be|Чарнобыльскі шлях}}, {{lang-ru|Чернобыльский шлях, Чернобыльский путь}}) is an annual rally run on April 26 by the opposition in [[Belarus]] as a remembrance of the [[Chernobyl disaster]].
The first time it was run in 1989 with demands of urgent efforts in eliminating the consequences of the catastrophe.<ref>[http://visualrian.com/images/item/767815 "Chernobyl Way"], a [[RIA Novosti]] documentary</ref>
On the 10th anniversary of the catastrophe the rally was held the first time during [[Lukashenko]]'s presidency. The rally was dispersed by [[OMON]] and its activists were arrested.<ref>Маховский А. «Чернобыльский шлях» преградили ценой жестоких столкновений. — Белорусская деловая газета. — 1996. — 2.05. — № 32 — С.1;</ref>
