[[File:Hotel Chez Lando.jpg|thumb|Hotel Chez Lando]]
'''Chez Lando''' is a hotel and restaurant located in the [[Rwanda]]n capital city, [[Kigali]]. The hotel was founded in the 1980s by prominent Rwandan businessman and politician [[Lando Ndasingwa]], and his Canadian wife Hélène,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.focus.rw/wp/2016/07/chez-lando-fire-causes-minimal-damage/# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022083841/http://www.focus.rw/wp/2016/07/chez-lando-fire-causes-minimal-damage/# |archive-date=2016-10-22 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> who were both killed in the 1994 [[Rwandan genocide]]. Following Ndasingwa's death, the hotel was taken over by his sister [[Anne-Marie Kantengwa]], who was a 2013 student on the [[Institute for Economic Empowerment of Women|IEEW]]'s Peace Through Business program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ieew.org/2013-ptb-students/anne-marie-kantengwa|title=the Institute for Economic Empowerment of Women – Anne-Marie Kantengwa|website=Ieew.org|accessdate=24 August 2017}}</ref>

