The '''Civil Guard Association for a Better Future''' ({{lang-hu|Szebb Jövőért Polgárőr Egyesület}}) is a Hungarian militant organisation involved in [[Anti-Romanyism|anti-Roma]] activities in areas such as the town of Gyöngyöspata in early 2011, where they have been accused of intimidating the Roma population with weapons and dogs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.humanrightsfirst.org/2011/03/18/hungarian-government-urged-to-protect-roma-from-harassment-and-intimidation/ |title=Hungarian Government Urged To Protect Roma From Harassment and Intimidation |publisher=Human Rights First |date=2011-03-18 |accessdate=2011-03-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110408060423/http://www.humanrightsfirst.org/2011/03/18/hungarian-government-urged-to-protect-roma-from-harassment-and-intimidation/ |archivedate=2011-04-08 |df= }}</ref>
The name originates from ''Szebb jövőt!'', the regular greeting of the [[Levente (organization)]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freepress-freespeech.com/holhome/kiscikk0/levente.htm |title=NÉHÁNY SZÓ A LEVENTEINTÉZMÉNYRŐL HUNNIA 115. szám |publisher=freepress-freespeech.com}}</ref>
The [[European Roma Rights Centre]] has claimed that the Civil Guard has ties to the Magyar Nemzeti Gárda, a new group sharing the same ideology as the banned [[Magyar Gárda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.errc.org/cms/upload/file/hungary-gy%C3%B6ngy%C3%B6spata-letter-march-2011.pdf |title=ERCC |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2011-03-28}}</ref>
