[[File:Nida kapines.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Krikštai at the ethnographic cemetery in [[Nida, Lithuania]]]]
'''Krikštas''' (plural: krikštai) is a [[Lithuania]]n burial monument of oldest type. Typically they are carved of wood. 

Old ''krikštai'' are usually symmetric figurines of horsehears, birds, plants, hearts, etc. Since 19th century cross-shaped monuments started to appear.


