'''National Highway 2''' — '''NH2''', or National Road No.2 (10002), is one of the national [[highway]]s of [[Cambodia]]. 

With a length of {{convert|120.60|km|abbr=on}}, it connects the capital of [[Phnom Penh]] with [[Vietnam]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060825003757/http://www.cambodiaportal.com/index.php?mymenu=destinations&submenu=nationalroadnetwork&ext=Y&submenutitle=National%20Road%20Network Cambodian national road network]</ref> 

NH2 leads south out of Phnom Penh, through [[Kandal Province]], and enters the [[Tram Kak District]] of [[Takéo Province]]. It continues south through [[Kiri Vong District]] in the province, where it veers due east and meets the border with Vietnam.

